Package executor.service.facade.execution

Interface ExecutionService

All Known Implementing Classes:
ScenarioWorker
public interface ExecutionService
Interface for defining an execution service.

This interface declares a single method, execute(), which should be implemented by classes aiming to provide execution capabilities. Classes implementing this interface are expected to perform specific actions or tasks when the execute() method is called.

Implementations of this interface can encapsulate various execution logic, such as running parallel flows, processing data, or triggering specific actions.
